Readings: ISCM with Nagios
A Security Operations Center (SOC) is a physical facility with an organization that houses an information security team. The team analyzes and monitors the security systems of an organization. The purpose of the SOC is to protect the company from security breaches by identifying and analyzing and then reacting to the threats. 

Nagios is a monitoring tool that is used to monitor the network in several ways. The tool is able to provide all the system-related information to the user and to also the real time monitoring of the network and application. Nagios is capable of monitoring the server and to find the performance hiccups if there are any. There are tools that you can use to monitor the statistics and send alerts to the admin. 


